<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>With just under two weeks until the international transfer window closes on October 5, clubs across Europe are looking to bring in flesh blood as the 2020-21 season starts to get going. </p>

<p>Chris Smalling, who has become surplus to requirements at Manchester United, will hope to resolve his future in the coming weeks, with the defender calling for a permanent return to Roma where he spent last season on loan.</p>

<p>Meanwhile Chelsea have drawn up plans to trim their squad after significant summer investment. Kepa Arrizabalaga, Antonio Rudiger and Ruben Loftus-Cheek are among the players who could be sold.</p>

<p>Sportsmail will provide live updates of the summer transfer window including permnanent signings, loan deals and latest negotiations across the Premier League and European clubs. </p>
